[1]
Date: 23 Dec 2012
Source: Prenza Latina [In Spanish, transl., edited by Mod.JG]
http://www.prensa-latina.cu/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&idioma=1&id=834391&Itemid=1


NHK, the main Japanese TV station, reported on 23 Dec 2012 that the death of 6 elderly subjects aged between 70 and 90 years old, apparently related to a gastrointestinal infection caused by a viral gene mutation [sic].

According to the available information, the deaths occurred in a hospital in Miyazaki Prefecture, southwest Japan, where other patients and workers have developed similar symptoms.

Medical authorities declared that at least 5 additional fatal cases have been detected in other unspecified regions. These deaths are thought to have the same cause, and it was pointed out that the mutant virus is rapidly spreading.

Both Miyazaki local government as well as Tokyo authorities indicated that extreme preventive measures have been taken, in order to stop the proliferation of this condition.

